def can_sort_using_swap(nums):
    for i in range(1, len(nums)):
        if nums[i] < nums[i - 1]:
            nums[i], nums[i - 1] = nums[i - 1], nums[i]
            if sorted(nums) == nums:
                return True
            nums[i], nums[i - 1] = nums[i - 1], nums[i]
    return False
```

    The algorithm starts iterating through the given array starting from the second element. It then checks if the current element is smaller than the previous one. If so, it swaps these two elements temporarily and checks if the resulting array is sorted. If the array is sorted, it returns true as it's possible to sort the array using the above swap method. If not, it swaps the elements back to their original positions and continues the iteration. If no swaps can sort the array, it returns false.

